1
00:00:04,215 --> 00:00:06,315
(Love In Sync)

2
00:00:13,155 --> 00:00:15,625
(Kim Myung Soo)

3
00:00:19,765 --> 00:00:22,295
(Kang Min Ah)

4
00:00:42,015 --> 00:00:45,185
(Love In Sync)

5
00:00:47,025 --> 00:00:48,094
(All people, incidents, and backgrounds...)

6
00:00:48,095 --> 00:00:49,224
(in this drama are fictitious and unrelated to reality.)

7
00:00:49,225 --> 00:00:50,425
(Also, children and animals were filmed under production guidelines.)

8
00:00:50,895 --> 00:00:52,695
Are you really going to close the clinic like this?

9
00:00:53,395 --> 00:00:54,395
There is nothing I can do.

10
00:00:55,035 --> 00:00:56,864
The result of the disciplinary appeal...

11
00:00:56,865 --> 00:00:58,605
won't be out for at least three months.

12
00:00:59,105 --> 00:01:00,835
What will you do in the meantime?

13
00:01:01,705 --> 00:01:03,575
Travelling? Studying?

14
00:01:05,045 --> 00:01:06,105
A side job.

15
00:01:06,915 --> 00:01:07,915
Excuse me?

16
00:01:09,015 --> 00:01:10,015
You know, right?

17
00:01:10,215 --> 00:01:11,615
Having multiple jobs is popular these days.

18
00:01:13,345 --> 00:01:14,715
What kind of side job will you do?

19
00:01:17,225 --> 00:01:18,225
As a manager.

20
00:01:19,055 --> 00:01:20,055
What?

21
00:01:23,695 --> 00:01:25,825
This contract follows the standard manager contract.

22
00:01:26,095 --> 00:01:28,495
Since it is a special situation, I added a few special clauses.

23
00:01:29,265 --> 00:01:30,265
Please check them.

24
00:01:36,275 --> 00:01:37,905
(Exclusive Management Contract)

25
00:01:41,775 --> 00:01:43,614
It's not the place which does cheating,

26
00:01:43,615 --> 00:01:45,245
so you don't need to feel distressed.

27
00:01:48,115 --> 00:01:49,185
Did you read my mind again?

28
00:02:01,295 --> 00:02:03,835
I clearly heard that the pay would be the best in the industry.

29
00:02:04,165 --> 00:02:06,405
I also clearly heard that you had enough money.

30
00:02:06,865 --> 00:02:10,475
I clearly stated the premise that it would not be as much as yours.

31
00:02:10,875 --> 00:02:11,875
But unfortunately,

32
00:02:11,876 --> 00:02:13,175
you would know that it's currently under provisional attachment.

33
00:02:18,745 --> 00:02:19,845
The contract period is exactly three months.

34
00:02:20,955 --> 00:02:22,184
Understood. By then,

35
00:02:22,185 --> 00:02:23,484
I will have successfully returned,

36
00:02:23,485 --> 00:02:24,725
and I won't ask you to stay for me.

37
00:02:26,685 --> 00:02:28,825
Do you have anything else you want to add?

38
00:02:32,295 --> 00:02:33,635
Just one thing.

39
00:02:34,935 --> 00:02:36,295
Please keep it a secret to my family.

40
00:02:37,105 --> 00:02:39,565
Especially to my sister.

41
00:02:42,375 --> 00:02:44,304
That is not difficult,

42
00:02:44,305 --> 00:02:46,245
but why are you so serious?

43
00:02:46,675 --> 00:02:48,415
You are scaring the person receiving the emotional transference.

44
00:02:50,345 --> 00:02:51,345
Indeed.

45
00:02:57,385 --> 00:02:58,385
Here.

46
00:03:09,395 --> 00:03:10,405
What is this?

47
00:03:11,035 --> 00:03:12,165
Did you not read the special agreement?

48
00:03:13,365 --> 00:03:15,034
It says that besides basic manager duties, you need...

49
00:03:15,035 --> 00:03:17,745
to cover my acting skills through emotional transference.

50
00:03:18,905 --> 00:03:20,104
I thought I just had to read the script and...

51
00:03:20,105 --> 00:03:21,575
transfer my emotions to you. Did I understand wrongly?

52
00:03:22,575 --> 00:03:24,885
Does this person think acting only requires emotions?

53
00:03:25,785 --> 00:03:28,085
Emotions, vocalization, physical expression.

54
00:03:29,855 --> 00:03:30,855
Sit here.

55
00:03:31,655 --> 00:03:32,655
Okay.

56
00:03:39,425 --> 00:03:41,564
Even if I receive emotions,

57
00:03:41,565 --> 00:03:43,704
it is important for us to work together...

58
00:03:43,705 --> 00:03:45,835
to give them my best performance, right?

59
00:03:50,845 --> 00:03:51,974
- Yes. - If you make me...

60
00:03:51,975 --> 00:03:53,644
feel the emotions, I will try to match...

61
00:03:53,645 --> 00:03:55,575
the vocalization and physical expression.

62
00:03:59,745 --> 00:04:01,585
Why do I have to do something like this?

63
00:04:02,455 --> 00:04:03,615
Let's not think like that.

64
00:04:04,855 --> 00:04:06,055
It's petty.

65
00:04:08,225 --> 00:04:09,955
Don't just carelessly leak my emotions.

66
00:04:10,695 --> 00:04:11,695
They're mine, after all.

67
00:04:13,065 --> 00:04:14,095
The copyright of emotions belongs to me.

68
00:04:17,405 --> 00:04:18,405
What can I do if I can't help hearing them?

69
00:04:22,035 --> 00:04:24,305
We're doing scene 19, which is in the dance studio.

70
00:04:24,575 --> 00:04:25,644
Hee Joo is packing her bag,

71
00:04:25,645 --> 00:04:27,914
and Yeon Ji is still holding out, not changing her clothes.

72
00:04:27,915 --> 00:04:29,745
If you smile to hide your emotions...

73
00:04:30,015 --> 00:04:31,245
Hee Joo must be packing her things.

74
00:04:31,715 --> 00:04:32,815
With a smile...

75
00:04:34,285 --> 00:04:35,955
You should think if you're smiling because you're happy...

76
00:04:36,185 --> 00:04:38,855
It says here, "with a smile."

77
00:04:38,885 --> 00:04:39,885
- Smiling because you're happy... - What?

78
00:04:42,195 --> 00:04:44,165
Me? Why?

79
00:04:45,065 --> 00:04:46,165
I can't dance.

80
00:04:47,195 --> 00:04:48,235
Well...

81
00:04:50,465 --> 00:04:52,534
So, the male lead's emotion here...

82
00:04:52,535 --> 00:04:54,235
is more like fear than hostility.

83
00:04:54,905 --> 00:04:55,905
Do you understand?

84
00:04:56,205 --> 00:04:57,574
- Yes. - Okay.

85
00:04:57,575 --> 00:04:59,545
Then you understood the male lead's character.

86
00:05:01,415 --> 00:05:02,615
By the way...

87
00:05:04,015 --> 00:05:05,845
What is the range of emotional transference?

88
00:05:08,555 --> 00:05:10,654
I mean, if we are at opposite ends of the Earth,

89
00:05:10,655 --> 00:05:12,355
will emotional transference really work properly?

90
00:05:13,125 --> 00:05:15,754
We need to know the possible range so that even if something urgent...

91
00:05:15,755 --> 00:05:18,125
happens on set, we don't go beyond that distance.

92
00:05:24,705 --> 00:05:27,705
Then let's test the range of emotional transference here.

93
00:05:29,005 --> 00:05:31,375
Shall we start with 1 square, 10 meters?

94
00:05:31,645 --> 00:05:32,705
Yes.

95
00:05:39,885 --> 00:05:40,885
Two.

96
00:05:43,585 --> 00:05:44,925
(Transferential in 10m Range)

97
00:06:07,915 --> 00:06:09,215
Ten.

98
00:06:12,315 --> 00:06:14,655
(Transferential)

99
00:06:17,525 --> 00:06:18,585
Here.

100
00:06:25,495 --> 00:06:26,895
I can't hear you.

101
00:06:27,265 --> 00:06:28,334
(Non-transferential)

102
00:06:28,335 --> 00:06:31,065
(The Maximum Transferential Distance: 50m)

103
00:06:42,975 --> 00:06:43,985
That must be the limit.

104
00:06:44,315 --> 00:06:46,114
That is right. It is not possible up to 60 meters.

105
00:06:46,115 --> 00:06:47,655
It seems to be possible exactly up to 50 meters.

106
00:06:48,285 --> 00:06:49,754
So, even on set, I should not be...

107
00:06:49,755 --> 00:06:51,225
more than 50 meters away.

108
00:06:51,525 --> 00:06:52,855
Then, you just should not be separated from me, Eun Hwan.

109
00:07:15,515 --> 00:07:17,885
Was my peace of mind...

110
00:07:19,215 --> 00:07:20,285
conveyed to you?

111
00:07:34,695 --> 00:07:35,695
Come in.

112
00:07:36,295 --> 00:07:38,005
- Ms. Yu Ji An. - Oh, yes.

113
00:07:46,645 --> 00:07:48,715
I am not really keen on it, but...

114
00:07:49,315 --> 00:07:50,844
our writer and director...

115
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:52,345
recommended you so much.

116
00:07:54,255 --> 00:07:56,585
I said her acting is better than expected.

117
00:07:57,355 --> 00:07:59,385
Just trust my judgment this one time. Okay?

118
00:08:00,585 --> 00:08:02,194
I'll see if it is worth carrying...

119
00:08:02,195 --> 00:08:05,195
that controversy. Let's see her acting.

120
00:08:47,305 --> 00:08:48,574
I passed the audition.

121
00:08:48,575 --> 00:08:49,775
I said I passed it.

122
00:08:49,835 --> 00:08:50,904
Passed.

123
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:53,805
- I got cast. - Passed?

124
00:08:54,115 --> 00:08:55,575
Did you pass the audition?

125
00:09:03,715 --> 00:09:04,725
Gosh.

126
00:09:06,285 --> 00:09:07,455
That's great. Congratulations.

127
00:09:07,755 --> 00:09:08,755
Gosh.

128
00:09:16,265 --> 00:09:18,164
To begin my work in earnest,

129
00:09:18,165 --> 00:09:19,465
I guess I'll have to buy a van, right?

130
00:09:20,165 --> 00:09:22,135
No. Should I hire a stylist first?

131
00:09:22,875 --> 00:09:24,045
Which shop should I go to?

132
00:09:24,475 --> 00:09:25,675
Why are you in such a hurry?

133
00:09:25,805 --> 00:09:28,145
It's just one drama casting that's been confirmed.

134
00:09:28,545 --> 00:09:30,515
Let's take it slow.

135
00:09:30,945 --> 00:09:32,045
You don't know what you are talking about.

136
00:09:32,945 --> 00:09:34,984
Soon, there will be magazine shoots, commercial deals,

137
00:09:34,985 --> 00:09:37,015
and even drama appearance offers pouring in.

138
00:09:37,785 --> 00:09:38,824
Excuse me?

139
00:09:38,825 --> 00:09:41,425
How common is an entertainer with star power as hot as mine?

140
00:09:42,255 --> 00:09:43,654
They might have hesitated...

141
00:09:43,655 --> 00:09:45,024
because they were mindful of the public,

142
00:09:45,025 --> 00:09:47,565
but now that the comeback signal has opened up. Then...

143
00:09:49,095 --> 00:09:50,805
(Receive, Reject, Message)

144
00:09:52,965 --> 00:09:54,104
- Hello, this is Cha Eun Hwan. - Are you the person...

145
00:09:54,105 --> 00:09:55,105
in charge of Yu Ji An?

146
00:09:55,605 --> 00:09:56,805
Gosh, yes.

147
00:09:57,445 --> 00:09:59,045
I am Yu Ji An's manager.

148
00:09:59,605 --> 00:10:01,715
I'm calling you to offer a photoshoot.

149
00:10:01,815 --> 00:10:02,815
What?

150
00:10:04,085 --> 00:10:05,445
A photoshoot?

151
00:10:19,565 --> 00:10:21,095
Yes, good. The pose is good now.

152
00:10:21,535 --> 00:10:22,594
Okay, good.

153
00:10:22,595 --> 00:10:23,595
We will go with that.

154
00:10:24,035 --> 00:10:25,504
Oh, that's pretty. Good.

155
00:10:25,505 --> 00:10:26,505
Stay like that.

156
00:10:26,665 --> 00:10:27,675
Oh, nice.

157
00:10:27,975 --> 00:10:30,575
Now, look the other way.

158
00:10:35,075 --> 00:10:37,545
(Kasavia, The Lens Which Makes Your Mellow Eyes)

159
00:10:37,915 --> 00:10:39,415
I am so dumbfounded.

160
00:10:39,715 --> 00:10:41,455
Do you think I am the same as before?

161
00:10:41,655 --> 00:10:43,055
You are mistaken.

162
00:10:43,615 --> 00:10:44,655
I am fine.

163
00:10:45,325 --> 00:10:46,725
It is stranger that you are doing this.

164
00:10:47,455 --> 00:10:48,495
You hurt my pride.

165
00:10:49,595 --> 00:10:51,524
No, I'm saying this...

166
00:10:51,525 --> 00:10:54,635
- because I misunderstood your... - There is no need for that.

167
00:10:54,995 --> 00:10:56,734
Do I really have to come out in this freezing cold...

168
00:10:56,735 --> 00:10:58,435
just to tell you that?

169
00:11:02,205 --> 00:11:03,934
("Yu Ji An Stars In 'Season of God,' a New Drama Made By...")

170
00:11:03,935 --> 00:11:05,275
("Writer Oh Jin Hee and Director Lee Dong Myeong")

171
00:11:11,515 --> 00:11:12,944
A character like Hee Joo,

172
00:11:12,945 --> 00:11:15,284
who always considers others' feelings first,

173
00:11:15,285 --> 00:11:17,255
would not readily get angry in this situation.

174
00:11:17,785 --> 00:11:20,285
So, even in that situation, she would unknowingly...

175
00:11:21,195 --> 00:11:22,795
just let out an awkward laugh.

176
00:11:23,395 --> 00:11:24,395
I see.

177
00:11:25,725 --> 00:11:26,795
Can you understand that?

178
00:11:26,895 --> 00:11:27,965
Yes.

179
00:11:29,395 --> 00:11:31,364
But how do you know...

180
00:11:31,365 --> 00:11:33,135
other people's emotions so well?

181
00:11:37,335 --> 00:11:39,505
Because I am a psychological counsellor, after all?

182
00:11:40,745 --> 00:11:43,345
Is that empathy innate?

183
00:11:44,285 --> 00:11:45,285
Or is it something you can learn?

184
00:11:47,315 --> 00:11:49,885
It is both innate and learned.

185
00:11:54,895 --> 00:11:56,655
My father was...

186
00:11:57,155 --> 00:11:58,395
that kind of person.

187
00:12:01,095 --> 00:12:04,265
Always putting others before himself.

188
00:12:06,265 --> 00:12:07,465
He passed away, right?

189
00:12:11,545 --> 00:12:16,575
I can feel that you are sad.

190
00:12:18,885 --> 00:12:21,085
Oh, yes.

191
00:12:23,015 --> 00:12:25,125
It was an accident in elementary school.

192
00:12:27,055 --> 00:12:28,155
That must have been hard.

193
00:12:31,265 --> 00:12:32,425
I didn't even deserve it.

194
00:12:34,465 --> 00:12:35,465
It was all because of me.

195
00:12:38,605 --> 00:12:40,005
It was just out of curiosity.

196
00:12:41,305 --> 00:12:43,805
I played with it out of curiosity and forgot.

197
00:12:48,945 --> 00:12:50,445
Don't cause trouble while Dad is working.

198
00:12:51,085 --> 00:12:52,345
Just give him the lottery ticket and leave.

199
00:12:52,685 --> 00:12:53,685
Understood?

200
00:12:53,685 --> 00:12:54,685
I said I got it.

201
00:12:55,715 --> 00:12:57,955
I said there was no problem, so let's proceed.

202
00:12:58,555 --> 00:13:00,125
Well, I'm telling you it's dangerous.

203
00:13:00,725 --> 00:13:03,555
No, the space is already cramped, and there's no ventilation.

204
00:13:04,265 --> 00:13:05,465
What if it rains later?

205
00:13:05,525 --> 00:13:06,795
I know, I know.

206
00:13:06,995 --> 00:13:09,095
It's not easy to stop filming here either.

207
00:13:09,565 --> 00:13:10,565
Director.

208
00:13:10,895 --> 00:13:11,905
Oh, well.

209
00:13:17,405 --> 00:13:18,505
Eun Hwan and Song Hwan.

210
00:13:20,105 --> 00:13:21,875
- What are you doing here? - Dad.

211
00:13:21,975 --> 00:13:23,044
Yes.

212
00:13:23,045 --> 00:13:24,115
What about your art competition?

213
00:13:24,645 --> 00:13:26,115
I couldn't go because of him.

214
00:13:28,115 --> 00:13:29,455
What are you doing there? Give it to him quickly.

215
00:13:31,525 --> 00:13:32,525
What is it?

216
00:13:33,625 --> 00:13:35,895
Eun Hwan was looking for toys in your room.

217
00:13:37,325 --> 00:13:38,765
The director is looking for you.

218
00:13:39,095 --> 00:13:40,095
Oh, really?

219
00:13:40,365 --> 00:13:41,395
Dad will be right back.

220
00:13:42,035 --> 00:13:43,035
Let's go.

221
00:13:49,605 --> 00:13:50,605
Take care of Eun Hwan.

222
00:13:50,675 --> 00:13:51,745
Dad, Dad.

223
00:13:52,675 --> 00:13:53,705
Dad, take this.

224
00:13:54,315 --> 00:13:55,315
No, Eun Hwan.

225
00:13:56,875 --> 00:13:58,685
I went to give it to him.

226
00:13:59,285 --> 00:14:00,515
Then the accident happened.

227
00:14:02,085 --> 00:14:03,515
Since that day, I always thought.

228
00:14:05,255 --> 00:14:07,655
If only I had not touched my father's respirator...

229
00:14:09,725 --> 00:14:11,524
No, if only I...

230
00:14:11,525 --> 00:14:13,325
If I had gone to give it to him alone...

231
00:14:15,535 --> 00:14:16,765
If only I had not...

232
00:14:18,765 --> 00:14:20,765
let go of my sister's hand at that moment,

233
00:14:24,475 --> 00:14:25,975
all this misfortune...

234
00:14:27,075 --> 00:14:28,645
would have avoided us.

235
00:14:31,615 --> 00:14:33,745
I am the one who made the biggest mistake.

236
00:14:34,715 --> 00:14:35,715
Why am I the only one...

237
00:14:37,985 --> 00:14:39,325
who is fine?

238
00:14:45,995 --> 00:14:47,265
But what right do I have to be struggling?

239
00:14:49,165 --> 00:14:50,165
How dare I.

240
00:14:59,145 --> 00:15:01,714
I am not that sad.

241
00:15:01,715 --> 00:15:03,075
Why are you crying so much?

242
00:15:04,445 --> 00:15:05,685
That emotional transference is malfunctioning.

243
00:15:07,885 --> 00:15:08,914
Tomorrow is the first shoot,

244
00:15:08,915 --> 00:15:09,985
and your eyes will be swollen because of me.

245
00:15:52,295 --> 00:15:54,225
Shall I tell you...

246
00:15:54,735 --> 00:15:56,165
a secret?

247
00:16:00,105 --> 00:16:02,375
If you make eye contact with me like this,

248
00:16:05,145 --> 00:16:06,945
the emotional transference stops.

249
00:16:19,555 --> 00:16:20,555
It is mine.

250
00:17:06,735 --> 00:17:10,635
How embarrassing.

251
00:17:21,555 --> 00:17:23,685
A kiss? What did I do to him?

252
00:17:24,855 --> 00:17:26,385
Should I just say it was a drunken mistake?

253
00:17:27,355 --> 00:17:29,295
Oh, I only drink sparkling water.

254
00:17:39,865 --> 00:17:40,865
What should I do?

255
00:17:41,335 --> 00:17:42,335
Gosh, I don't care anymore.

256
00:17:43,075 --> 00:17:44,105
I will just ignore it.

257
00:17:49,815 --> 00:17:50,815
Good morning.

258
00:17:57,715 --> 00:17:58,725
What was that?

259
00:17:59,285 --> 00:18:00,385
That sound just now?

260
00:18:01,595 --> 00:18:04,455
(To the actress with such controversy...)

261
00:18:08,795 --> 00:18:10,064
("Planning to Come Back Despite of The Controversy?")

262
00:18:10,065 --> 00:18:11,095
("Top Celebrity Yu Ji An's Moral Issue Is Reigniting")

263
00:18:17,335 --> 00:18:18,505
All right, we will get ready.

264
00:18:20,245 --> 00:18:21,245
All right.

265
00:18:22,545 --> 00:18:23,545
Ready.

266
00:18:25,345 --> 00:18:26,685
(Season of God)

267
00:18:29,955 --> 00:18:30,955
Action.

268
00:18:44,265 --> 00:18:46,065
- What is wrong with her? - Did she forget her lines?

269
00:18:46,165 --> 00:18:47,165
Should we show her the script?

270
00:18:47,665 --> 00:18:48,675
What is she doing?

271
00:18:48,735 --> 00:18:49,735
Is she sick?

272
00:18:52,645 --> 00:18:53,645
What's going on?

273
00:18:54,105 --> 00:18:57,045
Nothing at all... No emotions are conveyed.

274
00:19:08,355 --> 00:19:09,655
Yes, I am all ready.

275
00:19:10,725 --> 00:19:13,364
Don't rush at the kids too obviously.

