525
00:32:22,515 --> 00:32:24,185
Their words are all jumbled and don't make sense.

526
00:32:24,855 --> 00:32:25,855
You understand this much, right?

527
00:32:30,055 --> 00:32:32,425
But even when she was angry, her sentence structure was perfect.

528
00:32:33,065 --> 00:32:34,225
She didn't waste a single particle.

529
00:32:37,535 --> 00:32:38,535
It's not easy to do that.

530
00:32:39,605 --> 00:32:41,304
Especially for someone like Ji An,

531
00:32:41,305 --> 00:32:43,635
who lacks emotional control.

532
00:32:44,275 --> 00:32:45,675
Isn't it just because she's acted for a long time?

533
00:32:47,345 --> 00:32:49,575
It might become a habit for her to speak as if reciting lines.

534
00:32:52,385 --> 00:32:53,385
Exactly.

535
00:32:57,385 --> 00:32:59,154
I am just curious.

536
00:32:59,155 --> 00:33:00,925
Do your family know you act like this?

537
00:33:01,485 --> 00:33:04,095
She's getting angry as if she's memorizing lines.

538
00:33:04,655 --> 00:33:05,665
Are you crying?

539
00:33:05,725 --> 00:33:07,625
Hey, why are you crying?

540
00:33:07,765 --> 00:33:08,795
Why are you crying?

541
00:33:09,235 --> 00:33:13,164
(Just And Kind Police For The Public)

542
00:33:13,165 --> 00:33:17,105
(Just And Kind Police For The Public)

543
00:33:17,405 --> 00:33:18,605
Detective.

544
00:33:20,245 --> 00:33:22,944
– How have you been? – How have you been, Mr. Cha?

545
00:33:22,945 --> 00:33:24,944
I'm fine. I am sorry.

546
00:33:24,945 --> 00:33:26,815
I have another shameless favour to ask.

547
00:33:27,145 --> 00:33:29,555
If you ask something, it is always a go.

548
00:33:30,715 --> 00:33:31,715
What is it this time?

549
00:33:32,325 --> 00:33:33,725
Please find someone for me.

550
00:33:37,755 --> 00:33:38,755
Someone?

551
00:33:43,435 --> 00:33:46,005
(Shin Mi Jeong, Female, 26 years old)

552
00:33:51,235 --> 00:33:54,005
Auntie said Mom would be here.

553
00:34:04,455 --> 00:34:06,655
Why are you here?

554
00:34:07,455 --> 00:34:09,195
Can I go to the playground?

555
00:34:09,995 --> 00:34:12,594
– Playground? – Dad said I have to...

556
00:34:12,595 --> 00:34:14,525
get Mom's permission from now on.

557
00:34:15,695 --> 00:34:16,765
Did he?

558
00:34:17,735 --> 00:34:20,565
Then, will you go with Dad when he comes later?

559
00:34:23,005 --> 00:34:24,074
Why?

560
00:34:24,075 --> 00:34:27,045
I always go to the playground alone.

561
00:34:27,645 --> 00:34:30,445
I see.

562
00:34:31,715 --> 00:34:33,715
Okay, then go ahead.

563
00:34:35,045 --> 00:34:36,085
Don't be too late.

564
00:34:37,155 --> 00:34:39,285
Yes, I will be back.

565
00:35:30,105 --> 00:35:31,205
(Cheer up, Ji An. You got this!)

566
00:35:35,975 --> 00:35:36,975
I believe in you.

567
00:35:38,175 --> 00:35:39,185
You got this!

568
00:35:43,955 --> 00:35:45,685
(Cheer up, Ji An. You got this!)

569
00:35:47,325 --> 00:35:48,385
I have a mom too.

570
00:35:48,925 --> 00:35:49,954
That is a lie.

571
00:35:49,955 --> 00:35:51,025
You don't have a mom.

572
00:35:52,695 --> 00:35:54,124
Yes, I do. I told you I have a mom.

573
00:35:54,125 --> 00:35:57,195
If you have a mom, why do you play alone...

574
00:35:57,395 --> 00:35:58,795
at the playground every day?

575
00:36:00,635 --> 00:36:03,205
That is because my mom is...

576
00:36:05,745 --> 00:36:07,605
My mom is...

577
00:36:08,905 --> 00:36:11,115
That is because my mom is sick.

578
00:36:11,475 --> 00:36:12,885
See, she is a liar.

579
00:36:13,445 --> 00:36:14,445
She's an orphan.

580
00:36:15,345 --> 00:36:16,355
I am not an orphan.

581
00:36:16,585 --> 00:36:18,055
I am not a liar.

582
00:36:18,515 --> 00:36:19,525
Hey, did you...

583
00:36:20,085 --> 00:36:21,085
Hey.

584
00:36:23,695 --> 00:36:25,024
You can't fight...

585
00:36:25,025 --> 00:36:26,995
in this sacred playground, kids.

586
00:36:27,395 --> 00:36:28,395
Who are you, ma'am?

587
00:36:29,665 --> 00:36:30,665
Ma'am again?

588
00:36:31,095 --> 00:36:33,735
– Hey, I am not a ma'am. – She is my mom.

589
00:36:36,505 --> 00:36:37,535
Me?

590
00:36:44,645 --> 00:36:46,215
Oh, right.

591
00:36:46,985 --> 00:36:47,985
I am Ha Yul's mother.

592
00:36:49,115 --> 00:36:50,355
Who bothered Ha Yul?

593
00:36:50,985 --> 00:36:52,455
Was it you?

594
00:36:52,885 --> 00:36:53,885
Was it you?

595
00:37:07,935 --> 00:37:10,275
Little one, aren't you going home?

596
00:37:13,245 --> 00:37:14,245
Hey, it's late.

597
00:37:15,105 --> 00:37:16,844
If you don't go home again, your mother will worry herself...

598
00:37:16,845 --> 00:37:18,375
to death, thinking you might have been in an accident.

599
00:37:19,685 --> 00:37:21,745
My mother does not worry about me.

600
00:37:24,285 --> 00:37:25,985
Because she does not love me.

601
00:37:29,095 --> 00:37:31,994
No, there is no mother in the world...

602
00:37:31,995 --> 00:37:34,865
who does not love her child.

603
00:37:35,395 --> 00:37:36,565
You are lying.

604
00:37:39,105 --> 00:37:40,105
Yes, that's right.

605
00:37:42,005 --> 00:37:43,005
That's a lie.

606
00:37:46,605 --> 00:37:49,214
There are mothers who love...

607
00:37:49,215 --> 00:37:55,315
themselves more than their children.

608
00:37:57,085 --> 00:37:58,085
Like someone.

609
00:37:58,615 --> 00:37:59,625
Gosh.

610
00:38:00,055 --> 00:38:01,055
It's okay.

611
00:38:02,355 --> 00:38:04,255
I don't love my mom either.

612
00:38:05,295 --> 00:38:06,295
You are lying too.

613
00:38:08,195 --> 00:38:09,694
There are mothers in this world...

614
00:38:09,695 --> 00:38:12,195
who don't love their children,

615
00:38:12,435 --> 00:38:15,005
but there is no seven-year-old...

616
00:38:16,605 --> 00:38:17,605
who does not love their mother.

617
00:38:20,405 --> 00:38:21,405
I'm well aware of it.

618
00:38:28,345 --> 00:38:30,155
I am depressed and want to cook.

619
00:38:30,655 --> 00:38:31,915
Would you like to go to my place and eat tteokbokki?

620
00:38:33,555 --> 00:38:35,655
Are you happy? Let's go.

621
00:38:36,625 --> 00:38:37,625
You are cold, aren't you?

622
00:38:37,755 --> 00:38:39,295
Come here. Let's go.

623
00:38:41,065 --> 00:38:42,535
It's freezing.

624
00:38:45,765 --> 00:38:46,765
Ha Yul.

625
00:38:47,035 --> 00:38:48,335
It is Dad.

626
00:38:49,305 --> 00:38:51,135
Ha Yul, let's eat tteokbokki next time.

627
00:38:51,605 --> 00:38:54,245
Why? Can't we eat with Dad?

628
00:38:54,445 --> 00:38:56,614
No, we can't. See you next time then.

629
00:38:56,615 --> 00:38:57,615
Little kid next door.

630
00:39:05,925 --> 00:39:08,325
Ha Yul, where did you go with the aunt next door?

631
00:39:08,925 --> 00:39:10,295
We met at the playground.

632
00:39:11,155 --> 00:39:13,895
Dad, did you fight with her?

633
00:39:14,765 --> 00:39:15,765
No, why?

634
00:39:15,995 --> 00:39:17,695
She ran away when she saw you.

635
00:39:19,365 --> 00:39:20,365
Really?

636
00:39:22,405 --> 00:39:23,934
Ha Yul, do you want to have dinner...

637
00:39:23,935 --> 00:39:26,045
with Mom and the auntie today?

638
00:39:26,305 --> 00:39:27,605
What about Dad?

639
00:39:27,705 --> 00:39:30,375
Dad will have to go make up with her, right?

640
00:39:33,185 --> 00:39:34,315
Ji An, please open the door.

641
00:39:35,885 --> 00:39:38,885
Ji An. Ji An.

642
00:39:40,755 --> 00:39:41,755
Why? What?

643
00:39:41,755 --> 00:39:42,755
What?

644
00:39:42,955 --> 00:39:44,095
Why aren't you answering your phone?

645
00:39:44,195 --> 00:39:45,295
You made me worry.

646
00:39:46,295 --> 00:39:47,725
You were worried about me?

647
00:39:50,835 --> 00:39:53,564
If my celebrity is out of contact,

648
00:39:53,565 --> 00:39:55,065
wouldn't the manager worry?

649
00:39:55,535 --> 00:39:56,535
That's dereliction of duty.

650
00:39:58,235 --> 00:40:01,044
Now that you've confirmed the celebrity is alive,

651
00:40:01,045 --> 00:40:03,515
- you can go, Manager Cha. - What?

652
00:40:06,185 --> 00:40:07,345
Are you angry right now?

653
00:40:07,745 --> 00:40:09,715
No, I'm not angry.

654
00:40:13,485 --> 00:40:15,555
I think you are. I can feel it.

655
00:40:15,995 --> 00:40:16,995
I said I'm not angry.

656
00:40:17,495 --> 00:40:18,695
Why have you been looking at me like that?

657
00:40:18,755 --> 00:40:19,865
You are scaring me.

658
00:40:21,825 --> 00:40:23,165
Shall I tell you a secret?

659
00:40:24,035 --> 00:40:25,664
If you make eye contact with me like this,

660
00:40:25,665 --> 00:40:27,305
the emotional transference stops.

661
00:40:28,705 --> 00:40:29,805
You mean because of that?

662
00:40:30,375 --> 00:40:31,475
To stop the emotional transference?

663
00:40:33,505 --> 00:40:34,545
Gosh, that is really petty.

664
00:40:35,105 --> 00:40:37,314
You just let my emotions transfer to you without permission,

665
00:40:37,315 --> 00:40:38,444
but you are doing this...

666
00:40:38,445 --> 00:40:39,545
because you are afraid your emotions will transfer?

667
00:40:40,645 --> 00:40:41,885
So that is why you avoided my calls.

668
00:40:42,985 --> 00:40:44,255
Since you realise it, will you please leave?

669
00:40:44,715 --> 00:40:46,285
No, I won't.

670
00:40:47,025 --> 00:40:48,025
Come on. Let me go in.

671
00:40:55,265 --> 00:40:56,265
I knew this would happen.

672
00:40:56,365 --> 00:40:57,565
How much did you drink?

673
00:40:59,195 --> 00:41:00,205
Are you addicted to sparkling water?

674
00:41:01,665 --> 00:41:02,975
It is none of your business.

675
00:41:04,105 --> 00:41:05,945
I am not just anyone. I am your manager.

676
00:41:10,215 --> 00:41:11,215
Cook for me.

677
00:41:12,015 --> 00:41:13,985
Is this a restaurant? Why me?

678
00:41:14,185 --> 00:41:15,584
You said you feel better...

679
00:41:15,585 --> 00:41:16,855
when someone eats something delicious in front of you.

680
00:41:17,885 --> 00:41:19,655
So what?

681
00:41:20,455 --> 00:41:22,025
To make me feel better?

682
00:41:25,125 --> 00:41:26,195
What nonsense.

683
00:41:26,395 --> 00:41:27,395
Oh, hurry up.

684
00:41:46,285 --> 00:41:47,585
Will just one cup of tea be enough?

685
00:41:48,445 --> 00:41:51,754
I am used to it, so it is fine. In a disaster like this,

686
00:41:51,755 --> 00:41:53,525
I must maintain my beauty.

687
00:41:57,525 --> 00:41:58,955
I think you would be pretty even when you gain weight.

688
00:42:07,405 --> 00:42:10,405
It is not a heart-fluttering moment, but a thud.

689
00:42:11,105 --> 00:42:13,404
How can someone with such poor aesthetic taste...

690
00:42:13,405 --> 00:42:15,405
be my manager? What should I do?

691
00:42:16,445 --> 00:42:17,445
This way.

692
00:42:21,415 --> 00:42:22,415
Let's say that's true.

693
00:42:25,355 --> 00:42:27,825
So this is what it feels like for someone else to know my feelings.

694
00:42:30,295 --> 00:42:31,894
So you know...

695
00:42:31,895 --> 00:42:34,095
how uncomfortable I've been, right?

696
00:42:35,395 --> 00:42:37,764
And you know what a great sacrifice it was for me...

697
00:42:37,765 --> 00:42:40,535
to step up and be your manager despite that uncomfortableness.

698
00:42:43,075 --> 00:42:44,335
You're making a big deal out of it.

699
00:42:47,105 --> 00:42:49,275
You know I can hear everything.

700
00:42:50,075 --> 00:42:51,875
And you must also know that...

701
00:42:52,175 --> 00:42:53,685
I feel sorry for you.

702
00:43:00,455 --> 00:43:02,185
Are you really going to...

703
00:43:02,585 --> 00:43:03,895
give up to come back?

704
00:43:06,025 --> 00:43:08,495
You chased me around, begging for help with your comeback.

705
00:43:10,235 --> 00:43:11,695
I never chased you.

706
00:43:13,135 --> 00:43:15,365
It was just an active proposal.

707
00:43:15,765 --> 00:43:16,835
What?

708
00:43:17,535 --> 00:43:18,935
They said they don't want me.

709
00:43:19,975 --> 00:43:21,575
It's not about my acting skills.

710
00:43:23,845 --> 00:43:25,875
They say they hate my very existence.

711
00:43:27,545 --> 00:43:28,745
How can I make a comeback under that kind of reputation?

712
00:43:30,985 --> 00:43:32,685
And I won't be able to make a comeback for a while.

713
00:43:34,655 --> 00:43:36,994
If you try once like this,

714
00:43:36,995 --> 00:43:39,325
and then get forced out by public opinion,

715
00:43:40,025 --> 00:43:41,665
everyone plays it safe.

716
00:43:44,965 --> 00:43:45,965
What if I help you make a comeback?

717
00:43:47,565 --> 00:43:49,904
Within the three months as Ji An's manager,

718
00:43:49,905 --> 00:43:51,975
I will do whatever it takes to help Ji An make a comeback.

719
00:43:52,105 --> 00:43:53,245
And I will do that successfully.

720
00:43:55,405 --> 00:43:57,974
Just as I believe in myself this much,

721
00:43:57,975 --> 00:44:00,245
Ji An, you should also believe in yourself.

722
00:44:01,685 --> 00:44:04,485
Nothing has been revealed yet.

723
00:44:08,485 --> 00:44:09,795
(Leadership To Persuade Actors, Fans, And The Production Crew)

724
00:44:21,905 --> 00:44:24,605
Right, there is only one reason we gather here.

725
00:44:25,105 --> 00:44:27,305
To help Ji An make a successful comeback.

726
00:44:28,505 --> 00:44:30,444
After strategising all night...

727
00:44:30,445 --> 00:44:32,375
- Excuse me. - Yes, please speak.

728
00:44:32,615 --> 00:44:35,215
But why do we have to help her?

729
00:44:35,815 --> 00:44:38,755
Even Ha Yul and I.

730
00:44:43,095 --> 00:44:45,655
Of course. Yes, we must help her.

731
00:44:46,095 --> 00:44:48,095
- Yes, of course. - This will be fun.

732
00:44:48,165 --> 00:44:49,165
How exciting.

733
00:44:49,225 --> 00:44:50,235
Nice.

734
00:44:50,465 --> 00:44:52,794
The first strategy...

735
00:44:52,795 --> 00:44:54,665
for her comeback is...

736
00:44:56,535 --> 00:44:57,535
Take one each.

737
00:44:58,175 --> 00:44:59,875
Here.

738
00:45:00,845 --> 00:45:01,845
Look.

739
00:45:04,045 --> 00:45:05,115
(The Project For Yu Ji An's Comeback)

740
00:45:08,015 --> 00:45:10,085
A donation to the paediatric cancer ward five years ago.

741
00:45:10,655 --> 00:45:11,655
How did you find this?

742
00:45:11,785 --> 00:45:12,785
It was anonymous.

743
00:45:12,985 --> 00:45:14,954
I looked through Ji An's old records and...

744
00:45:14,955 --> 00:45:16,955
even interviews of hospital staff.

745
00:45:17,295 --> 00:45:18,495
You have quite a few donation records.

746
00:45:19,095 --> 00:45:20,665
There are many things I don't even remember.

747
00:45:21,365 --> 00:45:22,894
From now on, our job is to bring the...

748
00:45:22,895 --> 00:45:25,435
buried truth to the surface.

749
00:45:26,265 --> 00:45:29,004
We need to make people remember Ji An's true self,

750
00:45:29,005 --> 00:45:31,735
which they had forgotten or didn't know well.

751
00:45:32,605 --> 00:45:34,375
Shall we begin?

752
00:45:36,515 --> 00:45:37,675
Through various social media,

753
00:45:38,175 --> 00:45:40,214
creating natural buzz about Ji An...

754
00:45:40,215 --> 00:45:42,244
and favourable public opinion is the first step...

755
00:45:42,245 --> 00:45:44,315
to a successful comeback.

756
00:45:45,185 --> 00:45:47,724
Ji An's good deeds should be naturally...

757
00:45:47,725 --> 00:45:48,855
spread on social media.

758
00:45:49,655 --> 00:45:52,625
Will public opinion really change?

759
00:45:56,535 --> 00:45:57,565
We will make it change gradually.

760
00:46:01,735 --> 00:46:03,575
What are all these problems after recruiting a wrong person?

761
00:46:04,235 --> 00:46:06,135
Are you saying this video might not be true?

762
00:46:07,505 --> 00:46:09,175
The video itself was not manipulated.

763
00:46:10,175 --> 00:46:11,844
However, I will prove...

764
00:46:11,845 --> 00:46:14,715
that the video does not show Yu Ji An's power abuse.

765
00:46:15,615 --> 00:46:18,085
It will take more time to prove that,

766
00:46:18,685 --> 00:46:20,255
but please trust me just this once.

767
00:46:21,285 --> 00:46:22,555
All right.

768
00:46:22,625 --> 00:46:24,495
If you are so confident,

769
00:46:24,995 --> 00:46:26,295
let's go with the sole suspicion.

770
00:46:28,365 --> 00:46:30,594
Honestly, if it hadn't been for you back then,

771
00:46:30,595 --> 00:46:32,835
I would not have been able to continue working as a reporter.

772
00:46:34,235 --> 00:46:36,135
It seems it is my turn to repay that debt.

773
00:46:38,575 --> 00:46:39,975
Thank you.

774
00:46:40,245 --> 00:46:42,975
I will make sure you never regret that choice.

775
00:46:44,045 --> 00:46:46,215
Let's see.

776
00:46:48,585 --> 00:46:49,755
That's right.

777
00:46:50,285 --> 00:46:51,285
That's right.

778
00:46:51,415 --> 00:46:54,355
Yes. Last time, almost all of them were insults,

779
00:46:55,355 --> 00:46:56,525
but now it's half and half.

780
00:46:57,325 --> 00:46:58,325
Look.

781
00:46:58,895 --> 00:47:01,895
There are not many posts speaking ill of her anymore.

782
00:47:01,995 --> 00:47:02,995
Right?

783
00:47:04,495 --> 00:47:05,665
Check this out.

784
00:47:12,575 --> 00:47:14,245
(I hope she didn't do such things.)

785
00:47:23,555 --> 00:47:25,255
(Moon Gyeong Sik)

786
00:47:31,755 --> 00:47:34,024
So, Mr. Cha is...

787
00:47:34,025 --> 00:47:35,665
Yu Ji An's new manager?

788
00:47:36,265 --> 00:47:38,165
Yes, that is how it turned out.

789
00:47:39,665 --> 00:47:40,665
No, how did that happen?

790
00:47:40,965 --> 00:47:43,305
A counsellor and a manager don't seem related at all.

791
00:47:44,005 --> 00:47:46,744
Well, if I were to explain, it's a...

792
00:47:46,745 --> 00:47:49,675
bit of a long story.

793
00:48:00,385 --> 00:48:01,585
I think it will be difficult.

794
00:48:04,395 --> 00:48:06,964
Of course, I promised Mr. Cha,

795
00:48:06,965 --> 00:48:09,525
and I'm also ambitious about the actress Yu Ji An.

796
00:48:10,335 --> 00:48:12,894
But in this situation, even if I am the director,

797
00:48:12,895 --> 00:48:14,635
it's hard to push it unilaterally.

798
00:48:15,935 --> 00:48:19,774
You seem to have misunderstood something.

799
00:48:19,775 --> 00:48:21,304
I'm not asking you to cast Ji An unconditionally...

800
00:48:21,305 --> 00:48:23,545
with your authority as director.

801
00:48:25,445 --> 00:48:26,845
Just give her one chance.

802
00:48:28,615 --> 00:48:30,685
Let her audition for a supporting role.

803
00:48:31,215 --> 00:48:32,254
An audition?

804
00:48:32,255 --> 00:48:35,084
If Ji An earns the role through her skills at the audition,

805
00:48:35,085 --> 00:48:36,654
please ensure she can film without being removed...

806
00:48:36,655 --> 00:48:38,855
from the production, no matter what.

807
00:48:40,765 --> 00:48:42,765
That is all I ask.

808
00:48:44,995 --> 00:48:47,505
You want me to protect Yu Ji An with my authority?

809
00:48:50,535 --> 00:48:52,674
If she passes with her skills,

810
00:48:52,675 --> 00:48:54,345
I can take responsibility as the director.

811
00:48:55,045 --> 00:48:56,344
Anyway, last time,

812
00:48:56,345 --> 00:48:58,074
I let go of her too easily.

813
00:48:58,075 --> 00:48:59,175
I also feel sorry for that.

814
00:49:00,145 --> 00:49:02,815
But will Ji An audition for it?

815
00:49:04,415 --> 00:49:07,584
She was the top star...

816
00:49:07,585 --> 00:49:08,755
in Korea.

817
00:49:12,395 --> 00:49:14,894
Are you crazy? Even though I dropped out, I was...

818
00:49:14,895 --> 00:49:16,864
the original lead in that movie.

819
00:49:16,865 --> 00:49:18,534
But you want me to audition for a supporting role?

820
00:49:18,535 --> 00:49:20,065
No. I won't do it.

821
00:49:21,565 --> 00:49:23,835
The drama you filmed before was also a supporting role.

822
00:49:25,605 --> 00:49:26,605
That is true, but...

823
00:49:26,805 --> 00:49:30,474
Then why do you think it's so embarrassing...

824
00:49:30,475 --> 00:49:31,545
and hurt your pride about this?

825
00:49:31,945 --> 00:49:33,585
It is not that I am embarrassed or hurt my pride.

826
00:49:33,715 --> 00:49:34,885
It's that feeling. I can feel it.

827
00:49:37,755 --> 00:49:40,425
Because the female lead of the movie is Han Yi Jin?

828
00:49:41,428 --> 00:49:43,088
Is that so important?

829
00:49:44,655 --> 00:49:48,194
It is important. Since my debut, I have never...

830
00:49:48,195 --> 00:49:49,525
been pushed aside by her.

831
00:49:49,835 --> 00:49:51,995
- Then, get pushed aside this time. - What?

832
00:49:52,635 --> 00:49:54,134
Just because you haven't been pushed aside until now...

833
00:49:54,135 --> 00:49:55,565
doesn't mean you never will be.

834
00:49:57,141 --> 00:49:58,415
Look, Cha Eun Hwan.

835
00:49:58,440 --> 00:50:00,814
You have to experience being pushed aside and rejected.

836
00:50:00,839 --> 00:50:02,409
It will enrich your emotions.

837
00:50:03,475 --> 00:50:04,875
You said you want to act well.

838
00:50:05,375 --> 00:50:06,914
But how can you act well...

839
00:50:06,915 --> 00:50:08,015
if you don't even know such emotions?

840
00:50:10,355 --> 00:50:11,755
The role is good.

841
00:50:12,555 --> 00:50:15,485
I may not know about movies, but I know emotions well.

842
00:50:16,625 --> 00:50:18,654
Although it is a supporting role, there are many emotions...

843
00:50:18,655 --> 00:50:21,464
that can be expressed. If I convey the emotions to you,

844
00:50:21,465 --> 00:50:23,564
and Ji An expresses them well,

845
00:50:23,565 --> 00:50:25,865
I think you can be recognised by the public for your acting skills.

846
00:50:27,265 --> 00:50:29,504
You wanted to be a talented actress.

847
00:50:29,505 --> 00:50:31,335
You wanted to be a talented actress.

848
00:50:39,575 --> 00:50:40,585
Okay.

849
00:50:41,315 --> 00:50:42,515
This is as far as persuasion goes.

850
00:50:43,045 --> 00:50:44,355
I won't force you.

851
00:50:46,855 --> 00:50:50,055
How can I pass the audition without your emotional transference?

852
00:50:50,555 --> 00:50:52,355
Did you forget? The reversal?

853
00:50:54,865 --> 00:50:57,065
(The Note About The Days Of Emotional Transference)

854
00:50:59,065 --> 00:51:01,134
There must be some kind of rule...

855
00:51:01,135 --> 00:51:02,805
or reason we don't know about.

856
00:51:04,535 --> 00:51:05,634
But there is nothing in common between the day...

857
00:51:05,635 --> 00:51:07,744
the first emotional transference happened...

858
00:51:07,745 --> 00:51:10,915
and the day the reversal happened.

859
00:51:11,845 --> 00:51:14,514
The date, weather, time,

860
00:51:14,515 --> 00:51:17,055
place, situation... Nothing is the same.

861
00:51:24,955 --> 00:51:27,065
Why? Is there anything you can think of?

862
00:51:30,095 --> 00:51:31,095
Oh, no.

863
00:51:32,395 --> 00:51:34,205
Your face says otherwise.

864
00:51:34,965 --> 00:51:36,105
What is it? Tell me.

865
00:51:40,575 --> 00:51:42,645
Then listen without misunderstanding.

866
00:51:45,075 --> 00:51:47,285
- A kiss. - What?

867
00:51:48,015 --> 00:51:49,215
I said a kiss.

868
00:51:49,445 --> 00:51:51,084
The day the emotional transference began and...

869
00:51:51,085 --> 00:51:52,484
the day the reverse transference occurred,

870
00:51:52,485 --> 00:51:56,155
the only thing we had in common was a kiss.

871
00:51:59,925 --> 00:52:01,125
Gosh, that's not it.

872
00:52:01,795 --> 00:52:02,795
What did you hear?

873
00:52:05,735 --> 00:52:07,205
Where is this guy trying to pull a trick?

874
00:52:08,005 --> 00:52:09,864
- No. - My choice of words...

875
00:52:09,865 --> 00:52:11,335
was not that vulgar.

876
00:52:12,175 --> 00:52:14,145
Then do I look like I would not think that?

877
00:52:14,575 --> 00:52:16,044
You are lying in this urgent situation...

878
00:52:16,045 --> 00:52:18,815
- to kiss me once. - Lying?

879
00:52:19,475 --> 00:52:20,485
Do you think I am a fool?

880
00:52:22,445 --> 00:52:23,455
Well,

881
00:52:24,115 --> 00:52:25,754
I admit to the second one,

882
00:52:25,755 --> 00:52:27,355
but we didn't kiss the first one.

883
00:52:27,785 --> 00:52:29,725
I lost my mind for a moment, but did I lose my memory?

884
00:52:30,225 --> 00:52:31,225
To forget that kiss.

885
00:52:32,895 --> 00:52:34,195
We did. We kissed.

886
00:52:34,995 --> 00:52:36,064
What?

887
00:52:36,065 --> 00:52:37,065
When you collapsed.

888
00:52:40,905 --> 00:52:41,905
I am sorry.

889
00:52:47,905 --> 00:52:49,205
We did.

890
00:52:49,505 --> 00:52:50,715
We kissed.

891
00:52:51,245 --> 00:52:54,215
Then why did you run away when I kissed you?

892
00:52:55,515 --> 00:52:58,355
No, I didn't do the first one on purpose.

893
00:52:58,785 --> 00:53:00,885
I was just catching someone who was falling.

894
00:53:05,325 --> 00:53:07,395
What should we do now?

895
00:53:09,325 --> 00:53:10,335
Let's do it again then.

896
00:53:12,665 --> 00:53:14,305
Let's do it. The kiss.

897
00:53:14,965 --> 00:53:16,705
How can you suggest a kiss so easily?

898
00:53:17,975 --> 00:53:18,975
You don't know my profession?

899
00:53:19,135 --> 00:53:20,145
I am an actress.

900
00:53:20,375 --> 00:53:22,005
I am famous for filming kiss scenes well.

901
00:53:22,575 --> 00:53:23,744
All other male actors who filmed with me...

902
00:53:23,745 --> 00:53:25,975
are known as kiss masters in the algorithm.

903
00:53:27,285 --> 00:53:28,684
Yes, yes. You are so good at it.

904
00:53:28,685 --> 00:53:29,745
You are amazing.

905
00:53:30,415 --> 00:53:32,785
Of course. It means I am professional.

906
00:53:33,315 --> 00:53:35,325
How can you be good at kiss scenes but not other acting?

907
00:53:36,025 --> 00:53:38,525
So let's do it. The kiss. Like a business.

908
00:53:38,855 --> 00:53:40,665
Why me? I am not an actor.

909
00:53:40,725 --> 00:53:42,125
You are my manager.

910
00:53:43,795 --> 00:53:45,294
For my acting career,

911
00:53:45,295 --> 00:53:47,435
you will actively cooperate. Did you forget?

912
00:53:51,375 --> 00:53:52,834
If you feel it is unfair, then you can...

913
00:53:52,835 --> 00:53:54,675
think of it as practising acting together.

914
00:53:59,045 --> 00:54:00,285
If you run away this time, you are dead.

915
00:54:02,115 --> 00:54:03,115
It is work, just work.

